task.summary: Default task

Allows to choose children dataset of the WCOJ.
* to push semijoins under the WCOJ
Allows to run WCOJ with arbitrary number of children
Fixes tests, they should evaluate if a RDD is equal, not if the one-sided subtract is empty
Shrinked input set
Use require instead of assert
Deactivates Spark INFO level logging for testing
Adds recursive directory deletion useful for testing

Adds diamond and four clique query; fixes a bug in the LeapFrog join discovered in the correctness testing of the four clique; adds regression test-case
Also: * Adds implicit conversion from LeapfrogTriejoin to Iterator * limits the dataset for path query correctness test independently of the FAST option
Adds House, 5-clique and 6-clique query with correctness tests
Adds cyclic queries and correctness tests
Experiment runner
Repairs AmazonTriangleExperiment
Disables Spark logging for experiment runs
Adds new commandline experiment runner
Adds metrics to WCOJExec

Adds ability to load SNB and LiveJournal datasets.
Also: * caches datasets as parquet files to speed up loading * uses fully qualified path to load the datasets
Adds memory usage metric to ToTrieIterableRDDExec
Adds ability to run multiple algorithms
Adds ability to run multiple repetitions
Removes print statements
Adds ability to log WCOJ, copy and materialization time
Enables jar building
Allows to run on a brick
Optimizes output copying in WCOJExec
Optimizes output copying in WCOJExec, tell Spark that there are no null values
Adds main to profile leap frog trie join
Removes old logging line
Replaces Scala's expensive sort function with self-written insertion sort
Uses a map instead of linear lookup for trieJoinUp and trieJoinDown
Runs gc after each repetition, that decreases the variability of the results
Stub for different variable orders
Adds Java implementation of the GallopingSearch.
Adds TODOs for optimization ideas of meeting with Peter
Optimizes ArrayTrieIterable

Optimization, factors out some often used values in ArrayTrieIterable.
WCOJ, 0601, clique-5 131 --> 119 seconds.

Optimizes binary search, use linear search, uses one less branch in loop.
WCOJ, amazon0602, 5-clique 119 --> 105

Uses arrays instead of Maps.
WCOJ, amazon0602, 5-clique 105 --> 71

Uses arrays instead of Maps.
WCOJ, amazon0602, 5-clique 105 --> 71
Optimization, uses compiler optimizations and while loop foreach
Optimization, removes another Scala collections function call
Uses OffHeapColumnVector as backing datastructure
Allows to deactivate assertions
Cleans up Queries, removes old experiments
Prepares for distinct LeapfrogTriejoin

Avoids sorting on the last Leapfrog join if only a single value changed
Does not work for queries which have no intersection in the TrieIterators of the last two variables. This could be easily fixed because then no sorting is necessary at all.
Simplifies LeapfrogTriejoin statemachine

Uses private[this] to ensure field accesses instead of function calls
However, performance difference seems marginal

A predicated version of the main loop in LeapfrogTriejoin.
No measureable performance improvement.
